{
  "texts": [
    "On IFEval, which is already saturated by frontier models, RIFL also slightly improves the performance.",
    "These results show that RIFL can effectively enhance the model's ability to follow complex instructions, handle multi-turn conversations, and adapt to different system prompts.",
    "Qualitatively, we find that the vanilla LLM judge is prone to reward hacking issues, where the model learns to exploit the weaknesses of the judge to obtain higher rewards without truly improving its instruction-following ability.",
    "In contrast, the finetuned rubric verifier is more robust against such issues.",
    "See Section C for a concrete example."
  ]
}